data.content:
Here's what breaks in EF Core 10 and the fixes:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression trees no longer needed

The API now accepts `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`. Your complex expression tree code won't compile. Replace with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// .NET 10 fix
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified

Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF Core 10 appends a number to disambiguate (e.g., `Street1`). Nested types like `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now use the full path: `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin existing column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

Otherwise you'll get a migration that renames columns (and breaks existing data).

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)  // ← new parameter (redacted SQL)
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe output */ }
}
```

---

**Summary of actions:**
| Issue | Severity | Action |
|-------|----------|--------|
| `ExecuteUpdateAsync` signature | Build error | Rewrite as plain lambda |
| Complex type column naming | Silent migration diff | Add `HasColumnName()` |
| Diagnostics logger interface | Build error | Add `string logCommandText` param |
